description:
It's the grand finale! The showdown between Zemo and Bucky Barnes, and even if Bucky can survive a second trip to Zemo's island his world will never be the same after what the vile villain has done to it!

Also, the nefarious Grey Gargoyle, on a quest for immortality, sets out to attain godhood in Asgard! Thor, god of Thunder, must end Gargoyle’s rampage!

Plus, Iron Man vs. Detroit Steel! The fuse that was lit with Stark Resilient reaches an inevitable, explosive end! Tony Stark races for his life against an endless Hammer Industries fleet intent on killing him and destroying his greatest creation!

Includes material reprinted from Captain America #610, Thor Vol.1 #620.1 and Invincible Iron Man Vol. 5#32!

description:
The Scarlet Witch has been reborn, and reality is trembling! Is the resurrection of the world’s mutants at hand, or is disaster just around the corner? Don’t miss the shocks!

The Children's Crusade explodes as the Avengers and Magneto clash with Doctor Doom! Wolverine finds the Scarlet Witch, and he wants her dead!

A new epic is here: The Children's Crusade!

The Young Avengers return, and the search for the Scarlet Witch finally begins! Magneto clashes with the Avengers in a shocking story that will redefine the entire Marvel Universe!]

Solicit: The game is afoot, and a leg, and a fist and the whole darned body! The descendants of Sherlock Holmes and Dr. Watson continue the family business in modern times, serving Queen and country, battling diabolical villains and solving the big mysteries no one else dares to confront as agents of HOLMES INCORPORATED!

This issue is comprise of several stories that were created by the Toronto Cartoonists Workshop.

Night of the living: Trey Holmes and Elizabeth Watson battle scientifically made zombies by an unknown "mad" scientist. He himself takes the improved formula and trys to kill the woman only to be sliced in half by trey and killed...or was he?

Hologram Holmes: Arthur Holmes makes his grandfather a hologram of his father, the original Sherlock Holmes himself. It is programed with all the information the original Dr. Watson put in his log books. An unknown twist is when the hologram and his son have a heart to heart that they never had in life.

The Watson Files: Elizabeth writes of her unseal cases and struggles how to explain such tales.

The Terror of the Penitence House: Holmes Inc. Investigates an old house and are hunted by the ghosts of their past.

Analysis Paralysis: Edgar Holmes chastises Trey Watson and Elizabeth Holmes only to follow all the right clues to the wrong conclusion.

Special Guest: Arthur Holmes is attacked by a giant VAOS robot on television and he is able to defeat it the Re-Voltalizor.

Artie is Dead: Artie creates the Augmented Reality Technological Interface or A.R.T.I. It is a complete likeness of himself. One of his A.R.T.I. units was assassinated by Steve Venom. This allowed Artie to capture Venom and infiltrate the criminal organization as Venom himself. This action however led all of Holmes Inc. to think he was actually killed.

Full Time Voyeur: Ryan Preston and Trey Holmes test each other with their own mysteries.

Holmes Incorporated: This is a one page comic made to look like the back of an action figure blister of Number Two.

Flight Lessons: Artie falls for the beautiful Doctor Jasmina Nasim, but she is hiding a secret that can ruin everything.

Heroic Deeds: Edgar Holmes Sr. accounts the tale of when he severed on-board the H.M.S. Adler in World War II.

Little Trey in Slumberland: A young Trey dreams about her trip to the moon.

Drinking Buddies: Jerome sits in a bar and tells his many adventures with crime and the run-ins he has had with Holmes Inc.

Finally Peace and Quiet: Holmes Inc. set out for a day of fishing and relaxation as a young family years ago. Their holiday does not go as planed however when they run into a family who is missing their little girl.

Don't Stop Till You Get Enough: A funny story about Edgar Holmes Sr. hitting on a woman at his son's wedding.

Murder on the Moon: Edgar Holmes Jr. goes to the moon to rescue his old mentor Jasper. Things take a turn however when the clues lead Edgar closer to home.

Recipe for Chaos: Artie tries to uncover a counterfeit organization in Hong Kong who are making his toys into weapons. Unfortunately it is all a ruse by Olympia Kaos.

Holmes Incorporated: This is a one page comic made to look like an add. it depicts Edgar Holmes II easily defeating Margo the Magnificent.

*Note this book contains the first published work of Comicvine's own Silkcuts.

description: Ace Hart retitled as Space Ace from this issue.

Not exactly a normal little boy, Trout lives above a turnip factory. He goes on surreal adventures. And when a devilish puppet show comes to town, Trout seems to be the only one not to be taken in by the soul-nabbing show. It's up to him to find the truth and save the town before the traveling entertainers get away for good.
name: Trout

description: The evil puppet show from last issue is still in town and still has everyone's souls. Everyone, that is, except for the queer little boy Trout. But what makes Trout so special? Can he stop the puppet troop before they ensnare the entire town?

description:
Thor, god of thunder, has lived a life of divine luxury. After a night with Aphrodite, though, he wakes up to find his mighty hammer missing! Now, new gods are threatening to take over Olympus, Asgard, and more! Exiled to Earth, Thor must enlist the aid of Hercules, whom he always belittled, to look for the hammer and stop the new gods before it's too late!

Follow this "Godd Couple" as they strive to work together so they can survive an epic adventure of mythological proportions!

"Final Girl": A genre term in slasher films referring to the last person alive to confront the killer. Four young women mysteriously awaken in a seemingly abandoned town, accompanied by a group of fellow students. They soon encounter the unspeakable terrors the town conceals and are stalked by its horrific inhabitants. Though the girls desperately struggle to escape, only one of them will be the final girl!

Every page of this terror-tome is splattered in Hutchison's gore-drenched artwork, coupled with an unhealthy dose of black humor!

description:
Contents include:

Captain Falcon in Moon-Base Patrol, a space series drawn by Frank Black.

Escape from Earth, an adventure strip featuring Nazis plotting to escape into space as the downfall of the Third Reich approaches.

John Storm in Tarmac Base, featuring a test pilot flying a new high altitude jet outside of Earth's atmosphere. An adaptation of Dutch strip Piloot Storm by Dick Sprenger.

The Jungle of Space, an illustrated text story

Flash Gordon, reprinting the US newspaper strip

Johnny Hazard, also reprinting a US newspaper strip

Brick Bradford, reprinting the US Kings Features serial

St. Rockets, the Science College of Tomorrow, an illustrated text story

Space for Laughter, a jokes page including a half-page strip , Earthward Bound, wherein Gink Moony (King Moon) sends spies to Earth to steal cheese before his subjects devour the entire moon.

Professor Jack Ransom discovers the Seabed Citadel, an underseas adventure by Ley Kenyon.
